---
# COO Logging console plugin -> OpenShift console "Observe -> Logs".
# Points at OUR openshift-logging LokiStack. Admin-only is still enforced
# by the tenant RBAC: the console queries the lokistack gateway as the
# logged-in user, so dev-quarkus/dev-python are SAR-denied infra/audit and
# only cluster-admins (platform-logs-admin-reader) see platform logs.
# schema = the console plugin's LogQL query TEMPLATE (NOT a collector -
# there is one log source: the OTel DaemonSet via OTLP). On COO 1.4 +
# Loki Operator OTLP ingestion the console "otel" template does not match
# the stored stream labels; "viaq" does. Pinned to viaq via the var.
apiVersion: observability.openshift.io/v1alpha1
kind: UIPlugin
metadata:
  name: logging
spec:
  type: Logging
  logging:
    lokiStack:
      name: logging-loki
      namespace: {{ platform_logging_namespace }}
    schema: {{ platform_logs_ui_schema | default('select') }}
    logsLimit: 50
